<paragraph blockId="6.[151,586,151,178]" box="[151,586,151,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[151,586,151,178]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Acheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domesticus">
<emphasis box="[151,370,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">Acheta domesticus</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[378,586,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">(Linnaeus, 1758)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,224,322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">More common than previously thought. This species occurs in synanthropic environments, including rural settings.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,224,322]" box="[199,1093,295,322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">Distribution</emphasis>
. Widespread within the Palaearctic, Oriental and Nearctic regions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,729,403,430]" box="[151,729,403,430]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName authority="palmetorum (Krauss, 1902)" authorityName="palmetorum (Krauss" authorityYear="1902" box="[151,729,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Svercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="palmetorum" subSpecies="palmetorum">
<emphasis box="[151,540,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">Svercus palmetorum palmetorum</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[547,729,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">(Krauss, 1902)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1398,476,538]" box="[151,1398,476,502]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">Restricted to hydric and mesic habitats. More work to better define its local status and distribution is necessary.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1398,476,538]" box="[199,899,511,538]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">Distribution</emphasis>
. Mediterranean, extending to the Canary Islands.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,891,619,646]" box="[151,891,619,646]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName authority="bordigalensis (Latreille, 1804)" authorityName="bordigalensis (Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[151,891,619,646]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Eumodicogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bordigalensis" subSpecies="bordigalensis">
<emphasis box="[151,684,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">Eumodicogryllus bordigalensis bordigalensis</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[691,891,619,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">(Latreille, 1804)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,692,790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">Quite common locally, from a fairly broad array of habitats, ranging from mesic dry river valleys (seasonal run-off conduits) to agricultural parcels of land and other synanthropic environments.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,692,790]" box="[199,897,763,790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,763,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="113">Distribution</emphasis>
. Widespread across the entire Palaearctic region.
</paragraph>
